A fire that broke out in  Syria â€™s
Latakia prison killed 8 inmates and injured 2 members of the
security forces, the state-run  Syrian Arab News Agency  reported.  At 5 a.m. today, a prisoner set fire to blankets and other
items in one of the wings of the prison, the government agency
reported, citing Major General Kamal Fatih.  About 25 prisoners were hospitalized, according to the
report. The prison houses people incarcerated for criminal
